The paper deals with image retrieval using deep learning models, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel retrieval model that produces a dynamic embedding, which involves learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of current retrieval models and proposes a new approach, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also evaluates the proposed model using a comprehensive evaluation, which involves multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses a continuous control parameter to learn to reconstruct a dynamic embedding, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
